# EmailJS Configuration
# Sign up at https://www.emailjs.com/ and get your credentials
# Then create a .env file and add these values

REACT_APP_EMAILJS_SERVICE_ID=your_service_id_here
REACT_APP_EMAILJS_TEMPLATE_ID=your_template_id_here
REACT_APP_EMAILJS_PUBLIC_KEY=your_public_key_here

# Setup Instructions:
# 1. Go to https://www.emailjs.com/ and create a free account
# 2. Add a new Email Service (Gmail recommended)
# 3. Create an Email Template with these variables:
#    - {{from_name}} - Sender's name
#    - {{from_email}} - Sender's email
#    - {{subject}} - Message subject
#    - {{message}} - Message content
#    - {{to_email}} - Your email (Pranavs22638@gmail.com)
#    - {{to_phone}} - Your phone (8583064080)
# 4. Get your Public Key from Account settings
# 5. Copy this file to .env and replace the values
